Ad Text:
Data Analyst

Talenza's client is looking for a Data Analyst with strong Power BI and SQL experience - someone to design impactful dashboards, explore data with SQL, and help drive data literacy across the organisation.

Location: Brisbane, 2 days WFH

Employment Type: contract, 6 months + extension

Your role:

Gather and document reporting requirements from stakeholders.
Design, develop, and maintain Power BI dashboards using DAX and Power Query.
Use SQL for data exploration, validation, and analysis.
Collaborate on data models (star/snowflake) and ensure data accuracy.
Document processes, definitions, and reporting logic.
Deliver user training and support to promote self-service BI and data literacy.

Ideal Background:

Advanced Power BI features (DAX, Power Query, custom visuals...)
Strong SQL skills
Requirements management, documentation
user training.

Thank you for your interest. At Talenza we are passionate about providing equal employment opportunities and embracing diversity. Please note that we are only able to proceed with those who have full rights to work in Australia. Please apply directly or for a quicker response, contact Pierre Stordeur through LinkedIn

Who is Vivi 

Vivi is the only wireless screen mirroring and digital signage tool designed for education. We help IT help teachers help students with classroom technology that enhances collaboration, control, and creativity.  

Vivi exists because we all had that one teacher who changed our life, who went above and beyond to serve as a role model and sage. They guided discussion, connected with their students on a personal level, were just as engaging and entertaining as they were educational, and they created a dynamic learning environment by constantly involving students.

Those teachers are the masters of the social classroom. Personalised learning environments have been proven to deliver better educational outcomes for individuals through increased participation and engagement. To successfully create such an environment requires a fluid, visual dialogue between teacher and student. This is why Vivi exists. Vivi is used by over 825,000 teachers and students around the world and is setting out to disrupt the enormous education industry with our high-growth, ambitious, and creative team. In this rapidly evolving technology landscape, Vivi is always looking for new ways to disrupt the classroom experience, enhance customer experiences and expand globally.

Opportunity Overview:

This is a high-impact role where financial expertise and business acumen will help shape key decisions as we scale our operations and product offerings.

This role is hybrid and is 3 days/week in-office at our South Yarra location.

Collaborate with department heads to influence commercial decisions and drive profitability

Provide financial guidance on pricing, product launches and go-to-market strategies

Translate complex financial data into clear, actionable insights for non-finance stakeholders

Deliver monthly reporting packs with variance analysis and executive commentary

Build dynamic financial models to support scenario planning and investment decisions

Analyse key SaaS metrics including ARR, MRR, churn, CAC, LTV, and NRR

Partner with Sales and Marketing to assess campaign ROI and customer acquisition efficiency

CA/CPA qualified

Strong financial modelling skills

Exceptional communication skills and ability to present to the Executive Team

Commercial mindset with a passion for data-driven strategy

These Business Analyst roles focus on translating business requirements into ICT solutions to ensure appropriate ERP options are selected across each agency, facilitating operational efficiency and improved service delivery.

Working in a dynamic, multi-stakeholder environment, you’ll help address business impacts, risks, and requirements, supporting agencies in their journey to digital transformation.

Location - Canberra
These roles will be required to have 3 days on-site in Canberra each week with no remote options or interstate offices available.

ERP Technology

TechnologyOne
Aurion
Workday
Peoplesoft
(or other)

Engage with agency stakeholders to assess needs and translate business goals into clear, actionable ICT requirements for ERP solutions.
Develop detailed business requirements that are aligned with strategic objectives and ICT capacities.
Create user stories that accurately capture both functional and non-functional requirements, ensuring consideration for data management and compliance.
Ensure ERP solutions meet regulatory, legislative, and industry standards, providing business assurance throughout the transformation process.
Facilitate workshops and engagements that foster collaboration and enhance the success of ERP implementation projects.
Experience & Expertise

Demonstrated experience as a Business Analyst, preferably within government or HR Systems ERP-related projects.
Strong knowledge of business analysis methodologies and tools, with proven success in multi-stakeholder, complex environments.
Proficient in developing business requirements, user stories, and process flows that bridge business and ICT needs.
Excellent communication skills with the ability to engage effectively across diverse business and technical teams.
Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in Business, IT, or a related field (or years of relevant experience)
Certification in Business Analysis (e.g., CBAP, Agile BA) is desirable.
To be eligible, you must be an Australian Citizen, and hold an active Baseline clearance (NV1 clearance is desirable).

If you’re ready to drive change in a critical government transformation, apply today to contribute to this impactful ERP journey!

Category: Records Management & Document Control (Administration & Office Support)
Ad Text:
This well-established federal government agency plays a critical role in supporting transparency, compliance and sustainable management of nationally significant resources.
 
As part of a broader transformation, the organisation is preparing to transition to a new records management environment and is focused on enhancing information governance and operational efficiency.
 
The Opportunity

Working as a senior specialist within the Information Management function, you will lead the review and redesign of the agency’s current enterprise records management structure. This is a strategic and hands-on role where you will assess the current state, identify gaps and compliance risks, and design future-ready solutions to support a planned system transition in mid-next year.
 
The contract is initially for three months, with a likely extension through to the end of the financial year. Due to anticipated budget constraints, further extension beyond that period is unlikely. Full remote work arrangements can be supported for the right candidate.
 
The Role

Assess the current records management structure, identifying inefficiencies, risks and improvement opportunities
Consult with stakeholders to understand recordkeeping needs, workflows and compliance obligations
Design a classification scheme and information architecture that aligns to current and future systems (e.g. SharePoint)
Ensure alignment with legislative and governance requirements, including National Archives of Australia standards
Provide documentation, uplift guidance and knowledge transfer to internal staff
Contribute to transition planning to support implementation 
The Ideal Person

You’ll bring strong understanding of Commonwealth legislation and The ideal candidate will possess a deep understanding of Commonwealth legislation and compliance standards related to records governance. They will have demonstrated experience in managing information or records within complex or regulated environments, with prior work in the APS considered highly advantageous. Proficiency with Electronic Document and Records Management Systems (EDRMS), particularly tools such as Content Manager and SharePoint, is essential.

A strong analytical mindset is crucial, enabling the candidate to critically assess current-state issues and develop practical, forward-looking solutions. Success in this role also requires confident stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to influence and drive change in challenging settings. The candidate should be self-sufficient and resilient, comfortable navigating ambiguity and working independently to deliver outcomes.

To be eligible for this position, you must hold a Baseline security clearance.

Candidates must be Australian citizens to be considered, and clearance will be arranged for successful applicants.
 
Salary / Rate

$65/hr - $80/hr + 15.4% Super
How to Apply

To apply online, please click on the appropriate link.
 
Alternatively, for a confidential discussion, please Guy Butler-Manuel on 02 6108 4878 quoting ref no 21131.
 
HorizonOne is committed to building a diverse and inclusive workforce and we encourage applications from people of all cultures, capabilities and backgrounds.

Category:
Business/Systems Analysts (Information & Communication Technology)
Government - State (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
Computer Systems Officer Grade 5
2x Temporary Full-Time up to December 2026
Parramatta & Sydney Olympic Park


About us

The NSW Police Force (NSWPF) is one of the largest police forces in the western world, with more than 20,000 employees, including more than 4,000 administrative employees who support the sworn officers that provide a range of law and order services 24 hours a day, seven days a week to the socially, geographically and culturally diverse community of NSW.


About the role

We have an opportunity for 2 x Senior ICT Business Analysts to be part of our Project Managment Office, Technology & Communication Services Command. The role works with relevant stakeholders to understand business needs; capture, analyse and document requirements; and support the delivery of ICT solutions that meet business needs.

Join the PMO team at NSW Police Force as a Senior ICT Business Analyst and help shape the delivery of technology solutions that support critical policing and corporate operations. In this role, you’ll work closely with stakeholders to understand business needs, capture and analyse requirements, and support the delivery of ICT capabilities that drive strategic and operational outcomes. 

You’ll bring demonstrated high-level business analysis skills and significant experience delivering analysis across complex programs and projects. Your ability to conduct gap analyses, develop business cases, and translate technical concepts into plain language will be key to optimising performance and enabling continuous improvement. 

This role also requires strong knowledge of architecture frameworks and governance project management tools, along with the ability to lead integration of new capabilities into enterprise systems while maintaining alignment with organisational strategy

View the relevant role description for more information on this role (e.g. essential requirements, key accountabilities, key challenges and capabilities required for the role)

What we can offer you

At NSWPF our people have access to a range of benefits that help balance life at work and at home. Some of the benefits available when you join the NSWPF include:

competitive salary;
flexible work options;
opportunity to purchase leave;
annual leave loading;
corporate wellbeing programs including seminars and the Fitness Passport;
free annual influenza vaccination;
salary packaging options via superannuation contributions or a novated vehicle lease;
convenient location for public transport and to shops etc; and
in-house gym facilities. (Parramatta)

How to Apply

Applications can only be submitted electronically via the I Work for NSW website.

To be considered for this role, attach a cover letter (2 pages maximum) and an up-to-date resume that clearly details your skills & experience as relevant to this role.

Please do not attach copies of qualifications, certificates or documentation (other than what has been requested) - you can bring these if called for interview.

Please address each of the following Target Questions (500 words per question) in the text boxes provided in the online application or attach as a separate document.

Target Question 1:

Can you describe how you’ve worked across both technical and business teams to align ICT capabilities with business processes during a system enhancement or transformation project? What approach did you take to ensure the solution was scalable and strategically aligned with future needs?


Target Question 2:

Tell us about a time when you collaborated with internal stakeholders and external partners to identify and document business requirements for a new project. How did you ensure governance structures supported decision-making, accountability, and alignment with business objectives?

Your application must stand on its own merits, and the completeness and relevance of your application will determine if you proceed through to the selection process.

If you require any further information about this opportunity, please contact the hiring manager Shammi Rahman via (02)8835 9562.

To be eligible to apply for this role, you must meet one of the following statuses: 

an Australian Citizen;
a permanent resident of Australia; or
a New Zealand citizen.

Prior to commencement, the successful candidate will be required to undergo a rigorous National Police (criminal history) Check and obtain and maintain a Security Clearance as determined by the NSW Police Force.

Our commitment to Diversity:

The NSW Police Force is a proud employer of a diverse range of people. We are committed to reflecting the diverse community we serve and creating an inclusive and respectful workplace for all employees. Differences are embraced, contributions are valued, and everyone has a sense of connection and belonging.

We welcome people with diverse skills, experiences, perspectives and backgrounds and encourage applications from Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander peoples, and individuals who may identify as LGBTIQ, with disability, a culturally and linguistically diverse background, and people of all ages.

If you identify as a person with disability and require further information on the role or you require specific arrangements to participate in the recruitment process, please contact the HR Diversity Team by email at PCC-INCLUSION@police.nsw.gov.au.

If you identify as Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander and would like assistance with your application, please contact the NSWPF Aboriginal Employment & Engagement team at PCC-AEET@police.nsw.gov.au.

This recruitment may be used to create a Talent Pool for similar future roles (ongoing or temporary) that may arise over the next 18 months.

For more information on applying for roles with the NSW Police Force click here

Thank you for your interest in this role. We look forward to receiving your application.

Hello. We’re Virgin Australia. We’re the airline that’s always done things a little different. Our way. The Virgin way. We’re on a mission to make flying better than ‘nice’. And to do that, it takes a team of talented people who are passionate about customer experience, doing the right thing always, with a focus on safety – in the air, on the ground and in our workplaces. A team who values real diversity and inclusion, in a big brand with big ambitions.

 

What you’ll be doing:

As the Transformation Lead – Workforce productivity, you’ll be the subject matter expert driving the delivery of complex transformation programs that shape the future of our frontline employee operations. In this position, you will play a pivotal role in analysing data, and identifying opportunities to improve labour productivity to ensuring our workforce is optimally aligned to meet operational demand.

This dynamic position blends hands-on delivery with strategic program leadership, supporting Virgin Australia’s mission to build a more efficient, commercially focused, and engaging operation.

In addition you will:

Partner with key stakeholders across Cabin Crew, Flight Crew, Airport and Engineering and Maintenance teams, and internal teams to deliver transformation initiatives that drive efficiency and engagement.
Analyse workforce, productivity, and operational data to identify trends, opportunities, and areas for optimisation.
Develop and implement strategies to align the inflight workforce with operational demand, ensuring sustainable labour efficiency.
Support the design and delivery of transformation programs that improve performance, simplify processes, and enhance the crew experience.
Provide insights and recommendations to senior leadership to inform decision making and strategic workforce planning.
Collaborate with Finance and People teams to model workforce scenarios and track productivity outcomes.
Lead change management and communication efforts to ensure successful adoption of new ways of working.
Contribute to EA planning and drive the transformation agenda
Monitor and report on transformation program progress, identifying risks, dependencies, and required interventions.

 

You’ll be great in this role if you:

Possess 5+ years of experience in management consulting or a comparable analytical and transformation focused environment.
Have experience working within or alongside the aviation industry (highly regarded).
Demonstrate strong analytical and problem-solving capability, with the ability to interpret complex data and translate insights into actionable strategies.
Take full ownership of a portfolio of transformation initiatives, driving them through to successful delivery.
Undertake comprehensive research and analysis using internal and external data sources to inform evidence-based recommendations.
Lead and guide team members, where appropriate, in conducting analysis and developing program outputs.
Consistently deliver high-quality recommendations supported by robust data and sound commercial reasoning.
Prepare clear, accurate, and well-structured materials to communicate findings and recommendations effectively to stakeholders.
Proactively identify, assess, and manage risks and issues associated with project delivery.

 

What you’ll get from us

We’re committed to looking after you, with some of the best benefits and conditions in the industry – including (but not limited to):

Heavily discounted air travel for you and your loved ones (including $1000 worth of travel credits per year)
Flexible working arrangements (including work hours and work from home)
Discounts on travel insurance, car hire, accommodation and experiences worldwide
Discounted Virgin Australia Lounge membership
Hospitality, retail, technology, beauty services and wellness discounts
Wellness support, including the betterme digital wellbeing platform
A comprehensive Employee Assistance Program, which offers confidential coaching and support from qualified professionals for all aspects of life – physical, mental, social and financial
Dress for Your Day – enjoy the freedom to wear whatever is appropriate for the type of work you do and the day you have ahead of you 

Equality rules

We’re all individuals. We love that. That’s why we encourage applications from Indigenous Australians, people with disability, those from diverse cultural backgrounds, our friends in the LGBTQI+ community, and anyone else who wants to join our family.

Ready to apply?

We’re ready to hear from you. Apply now.
